        h4 What information do we collect? 
        p We collect information from you when you register on our site, place an order or subscribe to our newsletter. 
        p When ordering or registering on our site, as appropriate, you may be asked to enter your: name, e-mail address, mailing address, phone number or credit card information. You may, however, visit our site anonymously.


        h4 What do we use your information for? 
        p Any of the information we collect from you may be used in one of the following ways: 
        ul 
          li 
            p To personalize your experience (your information helps us to better respond to your individual needs)

          li 
            p To improve our website (we continually strive to improve our website offerings based on the information and feedback we receive from you)

          li 
            p To improve customer service (your information helps us to more effectively respond to your customer service requests and support needs)

          li 
            p To process transactions
            p Your information, whether public or private, will not be sold, exchanged, transferred, or given to any other company for any reason whatsoever, without your consent, other than for the express purpose of delivering the purchased product or service requested.

          li
            p To send periodic emails
            p The email address you provide for order processing, may be used to send you information and updates pertaining to your order.
            p You may also opt in to our email newsletter to receive occasional company news, updates, related product or service information, etc. Detailed unsubscribe instructions are included at the bottom of each email.


        h4 How do we protect your information? 
        p We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information when you place an order or enter, submit, or access your personal information. 
        p We store your information on a secure server. All supplied sensitive/credit information is transmitted via Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology and then encrypted into our Payment gateway providers database only to be accessible by those authorized with special access rights to such systems, and are required to keep the information confidential.
        p After a transaction, your financial information (credit cards, etc.) will not be stored on our servers.


        h4 Do we use cookies? 
        p Yes. Cookies are small files that a site or its service provider stores on your computer through your Web browser (if you allow) that enables the sites' or service providers' systems to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information.
        p We use cookies to help us remember the items in your shopping cart. And if you're a registered user, we use cookies to help us remember your login session, so you don't have to login every time you visit our site.

      
        h4 Do we disclose any information to outside parties? 
        p We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer to outside parties your personally identifiable information. This does not include trusted third parties who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you, so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential. We may also release your information when we believe release is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others rights, property, or safety. However, non-personally identifiable visitor information may be provided to other parties for marketing, advertising, or other uses.

    
        h4 Third party links 
        p Occasionally, at our discretion, we may include or offer third party products or services on our website. These third party sites have separate and independent privacy policies. We therefore have no responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked sites. We do not share any personally identifiable information through these links. Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our site and welcome any feedback about these sites.


        h4 California Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance
        p Because we value your privacy we have taken the necessary precautions to be in compliance with the California Online Privacy Protection Act. We therefore will not distribute your personal information to outside parties without your consent.
        p As part of the California Online Privacy Protection Act, all users of our site may make any changes to their information at anytime by logging in and going to their 'Profile' page at http://www.bitponics.com/account/profile.



        h4 Childrens Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance 
        p We are in compliance with the requirements of COPPA (Childrens Online Privacy Protection Act), we do not collect any information from anyone under 13 years of age. Our website, products and services are all directed to people who are at least 13 years old or older.


